# Trivy IaC findings that have been reviewed and consciously accepted.
# Each entry must carry a justification. Re-review periodically.

# AWS-0104: Security group rule allows unrestricted egress to 0.0.0.0/0.
# Accepted as the DEFAULT only. SAP NetWeaver/HANA hosts require broad outbound
# connectivity for OS patching, SAP software downloads, SSM Session Manager,
# EFS, and AWS service endpoints. This is now configurable: set
# `instance_egress_cidr_blocks` (root) or `egress_cidr_blocks` (sub-modules) to
# restrict egress for private/proxied networks.
AWS-0104
